[16:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description below. Also, this week, this AI is very useful for 3D reconstruction. So, it\'s called any recon and this can take a series of photos of a scene and it can reconstruct a 3D point cloud of'

[17:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the scene. The key here is you can just give it a bunch of images as FS2 and they don\'t even need to be perfectly aligned or captured in order and it\'s still able to output a coherent 3D reconstruction of the scene. So, you can'

[17:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just walk around and casually record stuff and it can reconstruct that into a solid 3D model. And that\'s a huge deal because traditional methods struggle when the input is sparse or inconsistent. Some newer diffusion-based'

[17:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'methods try to fix this by generating missing views, but they only usually look at one or two frames at a time and the results are inconsistent. This new any recon takes a different approach. It kind of keeps a global memory of the'

[17:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'scene. So, think of it like a continuously updated mental map of the 3D environment. So instead of forgetting earlier frames, it remembers them and uses them throughout the entire process. And so afterwards, it\'s able to fill in'

[18:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the blanks and generate a very coherent video and understanding of this entire scene. Here are some examples. Here we just input five different photos taken at random angles of this scene, and it\'s able to reconstruct it into a full 3D'

[18:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'scene. Or here\'s another example where we only have four photos of completely different areas at this location, but it\'s able to stitch them together very seamlessly. Or here\'s an even trickier'

[18:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'example where we only have two input views, but it\'s still able to stitch everything together and generate a very realistic 3D reconstruction of this scene. And if you compare this with other methods like ViewCrafter or Uni3C,'

[18:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which I\'ve gone over on my channel before, you can see that this new one is just a lot more detailed and coherent. The awesome thing is they\'ve released the code to this already. So, at the top of the page, if you click on this code'

